  "cooking_instructions": [
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Preheat the oven to 220°C/ 200°C (fan)/ gas 7</p><p>Take your <strong>chicken </strong>out of the fridge, open the packet and let it air</p><p>Heat a large, wide-based pan (preferably non-stick) with a large knob of <strong>butter</strong> over a medium heat</p><p>Once melted, add the <strong>curry powder</strong>,<strong> ground cumin </strong>and <strong>tomato paste</strong> to the pan and cook for 1-2 min or until fragrant – this is your <strong>butter curry paste</strong></p>",
      "order": 1,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-1-1661865928872-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-1-1661865928872-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-1-1661865928872-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-1-1661865928872-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-1-1661865928872-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Once fragrant, add <strong>half </strong>the<strong> butter curry paste </strong>to a small bowl and set aside for later</p><p>Add the <strong>remaining</strong> <strong>butter curry paste </strong>to a large bowl with the <strong>chicken breast portions</strong>, a very generous pinch of <strong>salt </strong>and a splash of <strong>cold</strong> <strong>water</strong></p><p>Give everything a good mix up – this is your <strong>marinaded butter chicken</strong></p>",
      "order": 2,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-2-1661865935055-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-2-1661865935055-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-2-1661865935055-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-2-1661865935055-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-2-1661865935055-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Transfer the <strong>marinaded butter chicken</strong> to one side of a <strong>baking paper</strong>-lined tray and put the tray in the oven for an initial 12 min</p>",
      "order": 3,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-3-1661865942701-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-3-1661865942701-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-3-1661865942701-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-3-1661865942701-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-3-1661865942701-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Meanwhile, tear the<strong> mini garlic & coriander naans</strong> into bite-sized pieces</p><p>Once the chicken has had an initial 12 min, add the <strong>naan pieces</strong> to the other side of the tray with a drizzle of <strong>olive oil</strong> and a pinch of <strong>salt</strong></p><p>Tip: Cooking for 4? Use 2 trays!</p><p>Return the tray to the oven for 7-8 min further or until the croutons are crispy and the chicken is cooked through (no pink meat!) – this is your <strong>butter chicken</strong> and <strong>naan croutons</strong></p>",
      "order": 4,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-4-1661865957264-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-4-1661865957264-x400.jpg",
